Yes, you can.  The URL <i>is</i> the version.  If you want a different version, you need a different url.<p>For example, when I released v1 of my package &quot;lumberjack&quot; you imported it with<p><pre><code>    import &quot;github.com/natefinch/lumberjack&quot;
</code></pre>
When I updated it to v2, I had to change the url. Luckily there&#x27;s <a href="http://gopkg.in" rel="nofollow">http://gopkg.in</a> to make this easy, so for v2 it&#x27;s<p><pre><code>    import &quot;gopkg.in/natefinch/lumberjack.v2&quot;
</code></pre>
Note that the above url actually redirects to the v2 branch of the same github repo.
